70 lbs in each hand
70 pounds in the Back Pack
120 on a sled
20 pound ankle weights 

Carry all of the weight for 1 mile without removing the pack.

#NeverGiveUp https://t.co/yENaNNGY7j

But for me I find strength from being able to share the journey and the struggles honestly with my family and close friends, from being outside, from training hard and getting cold regularly, from sunlight and fresh air, and from my Christian faith within.

Where do you get your strength from? Strength for the day ahead is something we all need in order to tackle the many obstacles that life throws at us. It’s important to choose wisely where we draw it. The clues are always in nature.

You’re doing it, you’re living it and you’re already winning. Simply to undertake is to achieve… 

#adventure #stateofmind #NeverGiveUp

The formal result, the societal accolades and self-imposed monuments are really the least important part of our life. True success comes through struggle and effort and giving our all. Some call it: never giving up. Either way, if you’re in the fight, keep going, be encouraged.

“Simply to undertake is to achieve…”
Sometimes there is so much pressure in life to somehow reach this mystical place called ‘success’. But the truth is that when we try and do our best then we are already winning. https://t.co/9uAWYVlgqY
